Description: Foot and some of lower wall of a large closed vase. Low, slightly flaring ring foot. Light buff-brown clay with calcite inclusions. Glaze band on outside of foot and lower wall. Red dipinto inscription under foot.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 658)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.664)
